# PR explain pages on Netlify (not in git)

Every pull request needs a **player-facing HTML description** deployed to Netlify — not just Markdown/HTML in the GitHub PR body.

**Do not commit the explain HTML** into this repo (`netlify-site/`, `pr*/`, gh-pages artifacts, etc.). Build it in a temp folder, deploy, then discard locally.

## Pattern

1. Write the page in a **temp dir** (e.g. `/tmp/pet-village-pr-{N}-explain/index.html`) in the PR-38 explain style:
   - Fonts: Press Start 2P + VT323
   - Sections: pill, TL;DR card, What changed, How to try it, Verification, PR link
2. Create a Netlify site named `pet-village-pr-{N}-explain` (e.g. `pet-village-pr-51-explain`).
3. Deploy **from the temp dir only**:
   ```sh
   npx netlify deploy --prod --dir=/tmp/pet-village-pr-{N}-explain --site=<site-id>
   ```
4. Put the live URL in the GitHub PR body (short summary + link is enough).
5. Leave the working tree clean of explain-page files — never `git add` them.

## GitHub PR body

Keep the GitHub description short. Prefer linking the Netlify explain page:

```markdown
Explain: https://pet-village-pr-51-explain.netlify.app

## Summary
- …
```

Do **not** treat the GitHub body as the primary HTML artifact — that lives on Netlify only.

## Examples already live

- https://pet-village-pr-38-explain.netlify.app
- Sibling repos use the same `*-pr-{N}-explain` naming
